Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Senior Software Engineer* role with *QXO*. I bring over three years of professional experience building full-stack eCommerce and platform services, AI-powered systems, and cloud-native backends, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the scalable, low-latency eCommerce platform engineering this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph that translates natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, object-oriented code structure, and reliable coordination across complex commerce workflows. To keep these systems production-ready, I implemented a full observability stack using LangSmith and Langfuse, covering tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks, and drove a 60% reduction in end-to-end latency and 50% reduction in LLM API costs through targeted performance tuning. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform with commerce and checkout flows built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS — delivering responsive, accessible UI components and scalable backend services as part of a cross-functional team serving thousands of users across 30+ applications. I also designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Java, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handled high-performance file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs, and built a personalization-driven support chatbot using LangChain and RAG that cut ticket resolution time by 20%. Together, these roles have prepared me to design, develop, and maintain eCommerce services and user interfaces that meet QXO's performance and reliability goals.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in data-driven model development and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture QXO values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I managed the full model lifecycle for StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion systems — from training on Pace's HPC cluster using CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA, to inference optimization with vLLM and deployment via Hugging Face. I also led workshops on GPU programming and building AI/ML agents with LangChain and LangGraph for 50+ students, which required breaking down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the knowledge-sharing and cross-functional collaboration this team values.

I have always been passionate about *never stopping building* and *winning customer loyalty through technology*, and I see QXO's mission to become the tech-enabled leader in the \$800 billion building products distribution industry as exactly the kind of high-impact, engineering-driven goal I want to contribute to. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

